                          <div class="date">Jan 18, 2018</div>
                          When it comes to naming colors, most people do so with ease. But, for odors, itâ€™s much harder to find the words. One notable exception to this rule is found among the Jahai people, a group of hunter-gatherers living in the Malay Peninsula who can name odors just as easily as colors. A new study by Asifa Majid (Radboud University and MPI for Psycholinguistics) and Nicole Kruspe (Lund University) suggests that the Jahaiâ€™s special way with smell is related to their hunting and gathering lifestyle. 
